name: dns
title: Google Cloud DNS API
description: Configures and serves authoritative DNS records.

schemas.name: DnsKeySpec
schemas.desc: Parameters for DnsKey key generation. Used for generating initial keys for a new ManagedZone and as default when adding a new DnsKey.

fields.name: algorithm
fields.desc: String mnemonic specifying the DNSSEC algorithm of this key.

fields.name: keyLength
fields.desc: Length of the keys in bits.

fields.name: keyType
fields.desc: One of "KEY_SIGNING" or "ZONE_SIGNING". Keys of type KEY_SIGNING have the Secure Entry Point flag set and, when active, will be used to sign only resource record sets of type DNSKEY. Otherwise, the Secure Entry Point flag will be cleared and this key will be used to sign only resource record sets of other types.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Identifies what kind of resource this is. Value: the fixed string "dns#dnsKeySpec".

schemas.name: ManagedZone
schemas.desc: A zone is a subtree of the DNS namespace under one administrative responsibility. A ManagedZone is a resource that represents a DNS zone hosted by the Cloud DNS service.

fields.name: description
fields.desc: A mutable string of at most 1024 characters associated with this resource for the user's convenience. Has no effect on the managed zone's function.

fields.name: dnsName
fields.desc: The DNS name of this managed zone, for instance "example.com.".

fields.name: name
fields.desc: User assigned name for this resource. Must be unique within the project. The name must be 1-63 characters long, must begin with a letter, end with a letter or digit, and only contain lowercase letters, digits or dashes.

fields.name: nameServerSet
fields.desc: Optionally specifies the NameServerSet for this ManagedZone. A NameServerSet is a set of DNS name servers that all host the same ManagedZones. Most users will leave this field unset.

fields.name: nameServers
fields.desc: Delegate your managed_zone to these virtual name servers; defined by the server (output only)

fields.name: creationTime
fields.desc: The time that this resource was created on the server. This is in RFC3339 text format. Output only.

fields.name: id
fields.desc: Unique identifier for the resource; defined by the server (output only)

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Identifies what kind of resource this is. Value: the fixed string "dns#dnsKey".

fields.name: publicKey
fields.desc: Base64 encoded public half of this key. Output only.

fields.name: description
fields.desc: A mutable string of at most 1024 characters associated with this resource for the user's convenience. Has no effect on the resource's function.

fields.name: digests
fields.desc: Cryptographic hashes of the DNSKEY resource record associated with this DnsKey. These digests are needed to construct a DS record that points at this DNS key. Output only.

fields.name: keyLength
fields.desc: Length of the key in bits. Specified at creation time then immutable.

fields.name: keyTag
fields.desc: The key tag is a non-cryptographic hash of the a DNSKEY resource record associated with this DnsKey. The key tag can be used to identify a DNSKEY more quickly (but it is not a unique identifier). In particular, the key tag is used in a parent zone's DS record to point at the DNSKEY in this child ManagedZone. The key tag is a number in the range [0, 65535] and the algorithm to calculate it is specified in RFC4034 Appendix B. Output only.

fields.name: type
fields.desc: One of "KEY_SIGNING" or "ZONE_SIGNING". Keys of type KEY_SIGNING have the Secure Entry Point flag set and, when active, will be used to sign only resource record sets of type DNSKEY. Otherwise, the Secure Entry Point flag will be cleared and this key will be used to sign only resource record sets of other types. Immutable after creation time.

fields.name: algorithm
fields.desc: String mnemonic specifying the DNSSEC algorithm of this key. Immutable after creation time.

fields.name: creationTime
fields.desc: The time that this resource was created in the control plane. This is in RFC3339 text format. Output only.

fields.name: id
fields.desc: Unique identifier for the resource; defined by the server (output only).

fields.name: isActive
fields.desc: Active keys will be used to sign subsequent changes to the ManagedZone. Inactive keys will still be present as DNSKEY Resource Records for the use of resolvers validating existing signatures.

fields.name: digest
fields.desc: The base-16 encoded bytes of this digest. Suitable for use in a DS resource record.

fields.name: type
fields.desc: Specifies the algorithm used to calculate this digest.

fields.desc: Type of resource.

In this way you can retrieve the complete contents of even very large collections one page at a time. There is no way to retrieve a consistent snapshot of a collection larger than the maximum page size.
